text: Anne Fergusson (born 11 October 1995) is a Canadian sitting volleyball player. She was a member of the Canada sitting volleyball team, at the 2020 Summer Paralympics. She competed at the 2015 Parapan American Games, where she won a bronze medal and 2019 Parapan American Games.
